For loops
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

for i in {1..10}
do
  echo "Hello World Iteration: $i"
done

break & continue
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
break >> jumps OUT of the loop
continue >> goes to next iteration in loop

while and until
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
while: runs while statement == true
until: runs unil statement == true

(in/de)crement example:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
increment: ((counter++)) ; ((counter=$counter+1))     #i++ ; i=i+1 ; i+=1
decrement: ((counter--)) ; ((counter=$counter-1))     #i-- ; i=i-1 ; i-=1

functions and while loops
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
function func_name () {
  counter=0
  while [[ $counter -le 10 ]] ; do
    ((counter++))
    ...
    ... ; done
}
